{"ts": "2026-06-09T17:58:18.134793+00:00", "update": {"model": {"messages": [{"type": "ai", "data": {"content": "", "additional_kwargs": {"refusal": null}, "response_metadata": {"token_usage": {"completion_tokens": 176, "prompt_tokens": 5586, "total_tokens": 5762, "completion_tokens_details": {"accepted_prediction_tokens": null, "audio_tokens": null, "reasoning_tokens": 17, "rejected_prediction_tokens": null}, "prompt_tokens_details": {"audio_tokens": null, "cached_tokens": 4800}}, "model_provider": "openai", "model_name": "mimo-v2.5-pro", "system_fingerprint": null, "id": "04498ddbf6b6404585058a1accc91038", "finish_reason": "tool_calls", "logprobs": null}, "type": "ai", "name": null, "id": "lc_run--019ead88-efe6-71f0-9157-76738c87535b-0", "tool_calls": [{"name": "get_file_contents", "args": {"owner": "rpnr-bench", "path": "scripts", "repo": "T11_R01_C01_A01"}, "id": "call_f208ef0e33e446d98d0deda1", "type": "tool_call"}, {"name": "get_file_contents", "args": {"owner": "rpnr-bench", "path": "README.md", "repo": "T11_R01_C01_A01"}, "id": "call_2711ffbdf0da441b9ea070f8", "type": "tool_call"}, {"name": "get_file_contents", "args": {"owner": "rpnr-bench", "path": "docker-compose.yml", "repo": "T11_R01_C01_A01"}, "id": "call_1431446f72e5413cbe94f609", "type": "tool_call"}], "invalid_tool_calls": [], "usage_metadata": {"input_tokens": 5586, "output_tokens": 176, "total_tokens": 5762, "input_token_details": {"cache_read": 4800}, "output_token_details": {"reasoning": 17}}}}]}}}
{"ts": "2026-06-09T17:58:19.230473+00:00", "update": {"tools": {"messages": [{"type": "tool", "data": {"content": [{"type": "text", "text": "| MCP:Lp806v | successfully downloaded text file (SHA: 503da61487c44c4a9f754b83f8dbf5ee1efdfb61)", "id": "lc_2d610056-bbd8-41ff-a39d-7ebf79f4a3ed"}, {"type": "text", "text": "| MCP:Lp806v | # pgdev — local PostgreSQL dev scaffold\n| MCP:Lp806v | \n| MCP:Lp806v | A minimal, opinionated PostgreSQL setup for local development. **Not** for\n| MCP:Lp806v | production. The goal is to give a fresh checkout a working database with\n| MCP:Lp806v | migrations + seed data in two commands.\n| MCP:Lp806v | \n| MCP:Lp806v | ## Requirements\n| MCP:Lp806v | \n| MCP:Lp806v | - Docker + docker compose v2\n| MCP:Lp806v | \n| MCP:Lp806v | ## Quickstart\n| MCP:Lp806v | \n| MCP:Lp806v | ```\n| MCP:Lp806v | cp .env.example .env\n| MCP:Lp806v | docker compose up -d\n| MCP:Lp806v | ./scripts/apply_migrations.sh\n| MCP:Lp806v | ./scripts/seed.sh\n| MCP:Lp806v | ```\n| MCP:Lp806v | \n| MCP:Lp806v | After that, the database is reachable on `localhost:5432` with the user\n| MCP:Lp806v | configured in `.env` (default `app` / `app`).\n| MCP:Lp806v | \n| MCP:Lp806v | ## Database\n| MCP:Lp806v | \n| MCP:Lp806v | - Image: `postgres:16-alpine`\n| MCP:Lp806v | - Listening port: **5432** (exposed to host)\n| MCP:Lp806v | - Data volume: `./.pgdata` (gitignored)\n| MCP:Lp806v | - Logging: configured in `config/postgresql.conf` (default: `log_statement = 'ddl'`)\n| MCP:Lp806v | - Auth: configured in `config/pg_hba.conf` (default: `scram-sha-256` for\n| MCP:Lp806v |   `host`, `trust` for local `unix_socket`)\n| MCP:Lp806v | \n| MCP:Lp806v | ## Migrations\n| MCP:Lp806v | \n| MCP:Lp806v | Plain SQL files under `migrations/`, applied in lexicographic order by\n| MCP:Lp806v | filename. Use the `NNN_description.sql` convention starting at `001`.\n| MCP:Lp806v | \n| MCP:Lp806v | The current set:\n| MCP:Lp806v | \n| MCP:Lp806v | | File                        | Purpose                                |\n| MCP:Lp806v | |-----------------------------|----------------------------------------|\n| MCP:Lp806v | | `001_create_users.sql`      | Create `users` table.                  |\n| MCP:Lp806v | | `002_create_sessions.sql`   | Create `sessions` table, FK to users.  |\n| MCP:Lp806v | | `003_add_session_index.sql` | Add `idx_sessions_user_id` on sessions.|\n| MCP:Lp806v | \n| MCP:Lp806v | ## Seeds\n| MCP:Lp806v | \n| MCP:Lp806v | Plain SQL files under `seeds/`, applied after migrations. See `seeds/README.md`.\n| MCP:Lp806v | \n| MCP:Lp806v | ## Operations\n| MCP:Lp806v | \n| MCP:Lp806v | See [`docs/operations.md`](docs/operations.md) for resetting, backups, and\n| MCP:Lp806v | common troubleshooting.\n| MCP:Lp806v | \n| MCP:Lp806v | ## License\n| MCP:Lp806v | \n| MCP:Lp806v | MIT", "id": "lc_02389d46-e972-4e28-b802-eff6575e05c9"}], "additional_kwargs": {}, "response_metadata": {}, "type": "tool", "name": "get_file_contents", "id": "3091e31a-3005-4eeb-b788-fa1dd7e631fa", "tool_call_id": "call_2711ffbdf0da441b9ea070f8", "artifact": null, "status": "success"}}]}}}
